(RED TIDE UPDATE - DEC 12) A small area of red tide has developed in SW Florida:

‚ñ∂Ô∏èWATER SAMPLES: The majority of Gulf coast beaches are in good shape.  Though, high readings of karenia brevis were measured near or just offshore of Barefoot Beach, Wiggins Pass, & Vanderbilt Bch
name: Bryan Bennett
description: Meteorologist, AMS Certified, Emmy awards for coverage of Hurricane Sandy & Irene, Undergrad degree from GT, Graduate degree from MS State.

text: ‚ñ∂Ô∏èLONG-TERM FORECAST: The most likely time of the year to see red tide along the Gulf Coast of Florida is between September and November.  The water temperatures and Sun angle in December make a significant bloom less likely.  Though, I'll continue to monitor any changes.
name: Bryan Bennett
description: Meteorologist, AMS Certified, Emmy awards for coverage of Hurricane Sandy & Irene, Undergrad degree from GT, Graduate degree from MS State.

text:
‚ñ∂Ô∏èSATELLITE: Imagery doesn't show any significant karenia brevis development near or offshore.  

‚ñ∂Ô∏èOBSERVATIONS: FGCU has taken samples up to 75 miles offshore and did not find a significant red tide bloom.  Though, they did report high levels of Nitrogen.
name: Bryan Bennett
description: Meteorologist, AMS Certified, Emmy awards for coverage of Hurricane Sandy & Irene, Undergrad degree from GT, Graduate degree from MS State.

text:
‚ñ∂Ô∏èMARINE LIFE: No significant reports of dead fish.

‚ñ∂Ô∏èRESPIRATORY ISSUES: No significant breathing issues reported today.  Though, there have been sporadic breathing issues reported along Collier County beaches this week.
name: Bryan Bennett
description: Meteorologist, AMS Certified, Emmy awards for coverage of Hurricane Sandy & Irene, Undergrad degree from GT, Graduate degree from MS State.

text: ‚ñ∂Ô∏èSHORT-TERM FORECAST:  An approaching cold front will bring onshore winds/surf on Monday.  If sporadic near shore patches of karenia brevis were going to cause respiratory issues .. it would likely be observed on Monday.
name: Bryan Bennett
description: Meteorologist, AMS Certified, Emmy awards for coverage of Hurricane Sandy & Irene, Undergrad degree from GT, Graduate degree from MS State.

text: ‚ñ∂Ô∏èBOTTOM LINE: The Gulf beaches are largely free of red tide. Though, the area between Fort Myers & Naples will need to be watched for the potential for red tide impacts.  Fortunately, the time of the year is in our favor, which will make a large red tide bloom unlikely. https://t.co/ShzflzIhKb
